==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mahratta
<hw>Mah*rat"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>Marhat⟦amac⟧</ets>, <ets>Marh⟦amac⟧tt⟦amac⟧</ets>, the name of a
famous Hindoo race, from the old Skr. name
<ets>Mah⟦amac⟧-r⟦amac⟧shtra</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of a numerous people
inhabiting the southwestern part of India. Also, the language of the
Mahrattas; Mahrati. It is closely allied to Sanskrit.</def> --
<def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the Mahrattas.</def></def2>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Maratha</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

